in <i>rapina</i>), used as a nickname for a rapacious person or a thief.","alternatively, a variant of   Rabin   2, a topographic name denoting residence on ravined terrain, ultimately of the same etymology as 1 above."]},{"name":"Raba","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Manfred.","Polish: status name from <i>rab</i> ‘servant; slave’, or an altered form of German   Rabe  . Compare Hungarian and Czech name   Rab  .","Czech: variant of   Rab   or a nickname from the dialect <i>rabit se</i> ‘to get excited’."]},{"name":"Raben","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Jewish Hymen.","German: from an ancient Germanic personal name containing the element <i>hraban</i> ‘raven’.","Jewish (Ashkenazic): variant of   Rabin  ."]},{"name":"Rabine","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Kurt, Reinhardt.","Jewish: variant of   Rabin  .","Americanized form of German   Rehbein  ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Rafin was born in 1055, in Warnham, West Sussex, England, United Kingdom. He married Mrs Rafin before 1080, in England. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 2 daughters. He died after 1086."},"et":{"1055–after 1086":"1055–pärast 1086","–Female":"Surnud","1080–Female":"1080–Surnud","1084–Female":"1084–Surnud","1086–Male":"1086–Surnud","1055–1086":"1055–1086","1080":"1080","about 1084":"umbes 1084","um 1086":"umbes 1086","1055":"1055","after 1086":"pärast 1086","1086":"1086","1084":"1084","before 1080":"enne 1080","Warnham, West Sussex, England, United Kingdom":"Warnham, West Sussex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"England","Warnham, Horsham, Sussex, England":"Warnham, Sussex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1055–after 1086":"1055–1086 jälkeen","–Female":"Kuollut","1080–Female":"1080–Kuollut","1084–Female":"1084–Kuollut","1086–Male":"1086–Kuollut","1055–1086":"1055–1086","1080":"1080","about 1084":"noin 1084","um 1086":"noin 1086","1055":"1055","after 1086":"1086 jälkeen","1086":"1086","1084":"1084","before 1080":"ennen vuotta 1080","Warnh